+// =============================================================================
+// LOCAL PATCH — Firefox launch concurrency throttle
+//   Patched by HushBox via patches/playwright-core@1.58.2.patch
+//
+// Bug being mitigated
+// -------------------
+// On headless Linux at high parallelism (>=6 simultaneous `firefox.launch()`
+// calls), Firefox content/GPU processes SIGSEGV with `ip == sp` NX-page faults
+// inside Mesa `llvmpipe-N` and `SkiaGPUWorker` threads. The firefoxUserPrefs
+// in e2e/firefox-launch-options.ts neutralize most of the JIT codegen path,
+// but a race window still exists between fork and Juggler-ready when many
+// Firefoxes initialize at once.
+//
+// Upstream tickets (all closed without a fix):
+//   https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/issues/3939   (2020)
+//   https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/issues/17876
+//   https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/issues/28896
+//   https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/issues/36551  (2025)
+// Playwright has no concurrency primitive in `BrowserType.launch`; only a
+// silent one-shot retry for glibc `ld.so` races at _innerLaunchWithRetries.
+//
+// What this patch does
+// --------------------
+// Caps concurrent firefox launches per Node worker to 3. Each Playwright
+// worker process has its own semaphore (module-scope state). Chromium and
+// WebKit are unaffected. Tests still run at the configured `workers` value;
+// only the in-flight `firefox.launch()` count is gated, so the throttle
+// applies only during the ~1s fork->Juggler-ready window.
+//
+// Why hardcoded N=3
+// -----------------
+// Matches the CI per-shard worker count (playwright.config.ts `isCI ? 3`)
+// and the patches config cap. Empirically the SIGSEGV rate goes to zero at
+// <=3 simultaneous Firefox launches in our environment; tuning is unnecessary.
+//
+// Removal criteria
+// ----------------
+// Delete this hunk when upstream Playwright either gates Firefox launches
+// itself or Mozilla ships a fix for the llvmpipe/Skia JIT race. Verify by
+// running `pnpm e2e --project=firefox` at workers='45%' on a 20-core box and
+// confirming zero SIGSEGV signals in the report.
+// =============================================================================
+const PW_FIREFOX_LAUNCH_CONCURRENCY = 3;
+let _ffLaunchInflight = 0;
+const _ffLaunchQueue = [];
+function _acquireFirefoxLaunchSlot() {
+  if (_ffLaunchInflight < PW_FIREFOX_LAUNCH_CONCURRENCY) {
+    _ffLaunchInflight++;
+    return Promise.resolve();
+  }
+  return new Promise((resolve) => _ffLaunchQueue.push(resolve));
+}
+function _releaseFirefoxLaunchSlot() {
+  const next = _ffLaunchQueue.shift();
+  if (next) next();
+  else _ffLaunchInflight--;
+}
